---
title: Chain of Custody
description: Standardized intake, transfer, and release processes to maintain admissibility.
---

{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}
  <section class="site-container py-12">
    <header class="mb-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Chain of Custody</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-700 max-w-prose">Document every transfer and handling step with audit records and role-based approvals.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="p-4 md:p-6 border rounded bg-white prose">
        <img src="/assets/images/service-custody.svg" alt="Custody icon" class="h-12 w-12"/>
        <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold">Provenance tracking</h3>
        <p>Track each actor, timestamp, and action for full provenance records.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 md:p-6 border rounded bg-white prose">
        <img src="/assets/images/service-audit.svg" alt="Audit icon" class="h-12 w-12"/>
        <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold">Secure transfers</h3>
        <p>Secure handoffs with cryptographic receipts and audit proofs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
